The paper deals with the problem of simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) in a deforming environment, which is a common problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for tracking non-rigid surfaces, which suggests the category cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the SLAM problem, which involves machine learning techniques, indicating the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the observability of the proposed algorithm, which is related to control theory, suggesting the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis and mathematical proofs, indicating the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
